Next actions:
1) Implement true rate-limit fallback flow: when a 429/rate-limit is detected, stop submitting/awaiting further concurrent LLM calls and process remaining unscored submissions sequentially (preferably with backoff).
2) Remove Streamlit/session-state dependencies from worker threads by passing immutable config into workers (mode, API key, rubric snapshot) and invoking pure scoring functions there.
3) Update live status to track actual in-flight futures (running set), not all pending items, so UI accurately reflects simultaneous work.